'''Darryl LeMon Glenn''' (born October 10, 1965) is an American politician and lawyer. He was the nominee of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]] in the [[United States Senate election in Colorado, 2016|2016 United States Senate election in Colorado]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denverpost.com/2016/04/13/darryl-glenn-looking-for-second-upset-in-senate-race/|title=Darryl Glenn looking for second upset in Senate race|last=Matthews|first=Mark K.|date=April 13, 2016|website=|publisher=The Denver Post|access-date=|work=denverpost.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazette.com/republican-u.s.-senate-candidate-darryl-glenn-has-tough-road-to-november-ballot/article/1577130He|title=Republican U.S.  Senate candidate Darryl Glenn has tough road to November ballot|last=Schrader|first=Megan|date=May 29, 2016|website=|publisher=Colorado Springs Gazette|access-date=|work=}}</ref> He lost to Democratic incumbent [[Michael Bennet]].

Glenn was formerly a [[U.S. Air Force]] officer, retiring as a [[lieutenant colonel]] after 21 years of combined [[Active duty|active]] and [[Reserve component|reserve duty]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coloradoindependent.com/159604/national-conservative-super-pac-buys-ads-for-darryl-glenn|title=National conservative Super PAC buys ads for Darryl Glenn|last=Hutchins|first=Corey|date=June 4, 2016|website=|publisher=The Colorado Independent|access-date=|work=coloradoindependent.com|accessdate=25 July 2016}}</ref> He was elected to the [[Colorado Springs, Colorado|Colorado Springs]] City Council in 2003 and in 2010 was elected as District 1 [[County commission|county commissioner]] in [[El Paso County, Colorado|El Paso County]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kktv.com/news/headlines/El-Paso-County-Commissioner-Announces-Candidacy-For-US-Senate-288716151.html|title=El Paso County Commissioner Announces Candidacy For U.S. Senate|last=|first=|date=January 15, 2015|website=|publisher=KKTV|access-date=August 22, 2016}}</ref> He was re-elected as commissioner in 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://blogs.denverpost.com/thespot/2015/01/15/el-paso-county-commissioner-wants-take-sen-michael-bennet/116389/|title=El Paso County commissioner wants to take on U.S. Sen. Michael Bennet in 2016|last=Bartels|first=Lynn|date=January 15, 2015|publisher=[[The Denver Post]]|accessdate=January 15, 2015}}</ref>

Glenn unsuccessfully ran for [[Colorado's 5th congressional district]] in [[United States House of Representatives elections in Colorado, 2018|2018]], against incumbent [[Doug Lamborn]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denverpost.com/2017/07/07/darryl-glenn-doug-lamborn-challenge/|title=Darryl Glenn planning to run for El Paso County congressional seat long held by Doug Lamborn|last1=Paul|last2=Matthews|first1=Jesse|first2=Mark K.|newspaper=[[Denver Post]]|date=July 7, 2017|accessdate=December 13, 2017}}</ref>

