{{Infobox person | image = Dotty-Lynch-journalist-D07 258 007a.JPG | imagesize = | caption = Dotty Lynch, professor at American University in Washington DC |birth_name = Dorothea Jean Lynch | birth_date = {{birth date|1945|7|24}} | birth_place = [[Brooklyn, New York]], USA | death_date = {{death date and age|2014|8|10|1945|7|24}} | death_place = [[Washington, DC]] | resting_place= | occupation = [[Political analyst]], [[academic]] | nationality = [[Americans|American]] | movement = | known_for = First female chief polltaker for a US presidential campaign | spouse = [[Richard Morgan Downey]] | children = | signature = | religion = | alma_mater = [[Marymount Manhattan College]], [[Fordham University]] <ref name=CBSNEWSobit>{{Cite web | last = Condon | first = Stephanie | title = Dotty Lynch, CBS News veteran and political trailblazer, dies at 69 | work = CBS News | accessdate = 2014-08-14 | date = 2014-08-11 | url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/dotty-lynch-cbs-news-veteran-and-political-trailblazer-dies-at-69/ }}</ref> | residence = | website = | footnotes = }} '''Dotty Lynch''' (July 24, 1945 – August 10, 2014) was an academic, journalist and political pollster, best known for being the first woman to be chief polltaker for a presidential campaign when she worked for [[Gary Hart]].<ref name=NYTObit>{{Cite news | issn = 0362-4331 | last = Vitello | first = Paul | title = Dotty Lynch, Pollster Who Saw the Gender Gap, Is Dead at 69 | work = The New York Times | accessdate = 2014-08-14 | date = 2014-08-11 | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/12/us/dotty-lynch-pollster-who-saw-the-gender-gap-is-dead-at-69.html }}</ref><ref> {{Cite web | last = Eggerton | first = John | title = Former CBS Senior Political Editor Lynch Dies | work = Broadcasting and Cable | accessdate = 2014-08-14 | date = 2014-08-11 | url = http://www.broadcastingcable.com/former-cbs-senior-political-editor-lynch-dies/133124 }}</ref> She also served as political advisor to [[George McGovern]] and [[Jimmy Carter]].<ref>{{Cite web | last = Burns | first = Alexander | title = CBS News veteran Dotty Lynch dies | work = POLITICO | accessdate = 2014-08-14 | date = 2014-08-11 | url = http://www.politico.com/blogs/media/2014/08/cbs-news-veteran-dotty-lynch-dies-193766.html }}</ref>
She was the [[CBS News]] senior political editor from 1985 to 2005 and was a member of the CBS News/New York Times polling consortium.<ref>http://www.american.edu/soc/faculty/dlynch.cfm</ref>
In 2006, she joined [[American University]]'s School of Communication as executive in residence, and became director of the SOC/SPA joint MA program in Political Communication.
== Career == Lynch began her career in 1968 when she worked as a researcher for the Election Unit at NBC. In 1972, she joined [[Cambridge Survey Research]], becoming a vice president in 1976.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Dotty Lynch Leaves Legacy of Political Communication | work = American University School of Communication News | date = 2014-08-12 | url = https://www.american.edu/soc/news/Dotty-Lynch-Political-Communication-Legacy.cfm }}</ref>
== Death == Lynch died August 10, 2014, from complications of [[melanoma]]. She is survived by her husband [[Richard Morgan Downey|R. Morgan Downey]] and stepson Robert.<ref name="NYTObit" />
