{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}
{{Use New Zealand English|date=July 2016}}
'''Gerald J. Ellott''' is a New Zealand architect and [[philatelist]] who signed the [[Roll of Distinguished Philatelists]] in 1988.<ref>''[http://www.abps.org.uk/Awards/Roll_of_Distinguished_Philatelists/RDP_Background_20111231_LR.pdf Background notes on The Roll of Distinguished Philatelists September 2011]'', Roll of Distinguished Philatelists Trust, London, 2011. [https://www.webcitation.org/6OlHSBOTl Archived here.]</ref> He is a member of the [[New Zealand Order of Merit]] (MNZM) for Philately and a past President of the [[Royal Philatelic Society of New Zealand]]. He is a member of the [[Royal Institute of British Architects]].<ref>[http://ellott-postalhistorian.com/ Gerald J. Ellott Postal History], 2016.</ref>

Ellott has been awarded the [[Fédération Internationale de Philatélie]] Research Medal.<ref>[http://www.aps.gen.nz/excellence.htm THE NEW ZEALAND MEDAL OF PHILATELIC EXCELLENCE] Auckland Philatelic Society, 2006. Retrieved 5 May 2014. [https://www.webcitation.org/6PLsQsPQn Archived here.]</ref>

Gerald's website [http://ellott-postalhistorian.com/ http://ellott-postalhistorian.com] was released on 26 July 2016 and contains over 70 articles saved in PDF files.

==Publications==
*''The Michael Sullivan Correspondence 1874 & 1882 to 1885''. Forces Postal History Society and Society of Postal Historians, 2007.

