[[File:Silesia Helena Antonia of Liège.jpg|thumb|Portrait of Helena Antonia of Liège]] [[Image:Helena Antonia.jpg|thumb|334px|Helena Antonia and other courtier women]] '''Helena Antonia''' (1550–1595) was a [[Bearded lady|bearded]] female [[court dwarf]] of [[Maria of Austria, Holy Roman Empress]] and was a favorite of [[Margaret of Austria, Queen of Spain]],<ref>Peterkin, Allan (2001). [https://books.google.com/books?id=7pdN3PnqOwMC&pg=PA101&dq= ''One Thousand Beards: A Cultural History of Facial Hair'']. Arsenal pulp press. p. 101. {{ISBN|1551521075}}</ref> and also a lady-in-waiting for [[Constance of Austria]]. She was born in [[Liège]].<Ref name="source1">Ulmus, Marcus Antonius. [https://books.google.com/books?id=2ztRKjT1SrAC&pg=PA307&dq#v=onepage&q&f=false Physiologia barbae humanae], p. 307 (1603)</ref><Ref name="ref2">Reynolds, Reginald. [https://books.google.com/books?ei=2AMuUsO8CqvA4AP_qoH4BQ&id=d-ffAAAAMAAJ&dq=helena+antonia+ulmus&q=helena+antonia#search_anchor Beards: Their Social Standing, Religious Involvements, Decorative Possibilities, and Value Offence and Defence Through the Ages], p. 291 (1950) ("Ulmus [has] useful information, showing the royal patronage often offered to bearded ladies.... and the bearded Helena Antonia, according to Ulmus (p. 307) was a special favourite of Margarita of Austria, later Queen of Spain.")</ref><Ref name="print3">[http://collection.waddesdon.org.uk/search.do;jsessionid=zhgtXxUrgPY0weNqOyT4rbhL.undefined?id=42537&db=object&page=1&view=detail Souvenir Print of Helena Antonia, Bearded Lady at the Court of the Archduchess of Austria, Maria of Spain], waddesdon.org.uk, Retrieved 10 September 2013</ref>
