{{Orphan|date=January 2018}}

'''Mariam Mint Ahmed Aicha''' is a [[Mauritania]]n politician. Her name is sometimes given as '''Mariam Mint Ahmed Aiche''' or '''Mariam bint Ahmed Aiche'''. From 1992 until 1994 she served as Minister of Women's Affairs; from 1994 until 1995 she was Secretary of Women's Affairs.<ref name="Sheldon2005">{{cite book|author=Kathleen E. Sheldon|title=Historical Dictionary of Women in Sub-Saharan Africa|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=36BViNOAu3sC|year=2005|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-5331-7}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guide2womenleaders.com/Mauritana.htm|title=Mauritania Ministers|website=www.guide2womenleaders.com|accessdate=27 October 2017}}</ref>

