'''Robin Scorpio''' is a [[fictional character]] from the [[ABC Daytime]] [[soap opera]] ''[[General Hospital]]'' and its primetime [[SOAPnet]] [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] ''[[General Hospital: Night Shift]]'', originated and portrayed by [[Kimberly McCullough]] on and off for [[list of longest-serving soap opera actors#United States|over 30 years]] since 1985.<ref name="SOD stats">{{cite web|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/features/general-hospital/soapstarstats/kimberlymccullough/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100710070932/http://www.soapoperadigest.com/features/general-hospital/soapstarstats/kimberlymccullough/|archivedate=July 10, 2010 |title=SOAP STAR STATS: Kimberly McCullough (Robin, 'GH')|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]] |publisher=SoapOperaDigest.com|accessdate=August 9, 2009}}</ref> The character came to mainstream attention during a 1990s story arc where her boyfriend [[Stone Cates]] dies from [[AIDS]] and Robin is diagnosed as [[HIV]]-positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mediacommons.futureofthebook.org/imr/2012/02/15/love-and-aids-afternoon|title=Love and AIDS in the Afternoon|publisher=In Media Res: A MediaCommons Project|accessdate=August 18, 2012}}</ref><ref name="Wrap" /> Robin is also famous in the soap community for having been one of the few long-term soap characters to age in real time, not [[SORAS]]ed like most other child actors.<ref name="Aurthur">{{cite news|last=Aurthur|first=Kate|title=Prepare the O.R. (and A.A.): Dr. Drake Is Back|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=November 30, 2005|publisher=nytimes.com|accessdate=August 24, 2012|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/11/30/arts/television/30soap.html}}</ref>

==Casting==
A seven-year-old McCullough was one of three actresses narrowed down for the part of five-year-old Robin, and was brought in to screen test with her on-screen parents [[Finola Hughes]] ([[Anna Devane]]) and [[Tristan Rogers]] ([[Robert Scorpio]]).<ref name="MSN Interview">{{cite web|last=Barnert|first=Deanna|title=McCullough and Hughes Talk Reunion and Robin's Exit|url=http://social.entertainment.msn.com/tv/blogs/tv-buzz-blogpost.aspx?post=c5db4f9f-8964-4a55-8bdc-9255ccdc7842|work=[[MSN TV]]|publisher=social.entertainment.msn.com|accessdate=September 9, 2012|date=February 8, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120221020045/http://social.entertainment.msn.com/tv/blogs/tv-buzz-blogpost.aspx?post=c5db4f9f-8964-4a55-8bdc-9255ccdc7842|archivedate=February 21, 2012|df=}}</ref> Hughes recalled the event to [[MSN TV]]: "We just started improvising with her, like anything. We were throwing things at her and she was just talking away. Tristan and I were looking at each other over her head going, 'This is it! This is what we wanted.'"<ref name="MSN Interview" /> Improvisation skills were key for ''General Hospital'''s process in the 1980s. As Hughes explained: "It was very improvised. Very loose. We used to just talk around the plot and maybe every now and again dip our toe in the actual storyline."<ref name="MSN Interview" />

McCullough debuted on September 6, 1985, and stayed with the series until September 12, 1996.<ref name="SOD stats"/> Afterwards, she returned as a series regular for brief stints: January 17, 1997 to February 3, 1997; March 12, 1997 to April 8, 1997; June 23, 1997 to August 8, 1997; December 11, 1997 to January 20, 1999; June 20–21, 2000 (for [[Port Charles (fictional city)#The Nurses.27 Ball|The Nurses' Ball]]); and July 16, 2004. She appeared on "[[Port Charles]]" in 1998, for one episode.<ref name="SOD stats"/> She also appeared on May 30 to June 4, 2001 on ''[[All My Children]]'' when Robin reunited with her mother Anna. McCullough returned to General Hospital as Robin on July 16, 2004 for the funeral of [[Lila Quartermaine]]	before rejoining the soap full-time on October 12, 2005.<ref name="TVG 2005">{{cite web|title=Did TVGuide.com call it or what?...|url=http://www.tvguide.com/soaps/Did-TVGuidecom-56094.aspx|work=[[TV Guide]]|publisher=tvguide.com|accessdate=August 25, 2012|author=TV Guide News|date=August 31, 2005}}</ref> She also appeared on both seasons of the spin-off series ''General Hospital: Night Shift'' in 2007 and 2008.<ref name="SOD stats"/>

For her work as Robin, McCullough has won two [[Daytime Emmy Award]]s, one for Outstanding Juvenile Female in 1989 and one for Outstanding Younger Actress in 1996.<ref name="SOD stats"/><ref name="Emmy 1989">{{cite web|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/Emmys/winners1989/index.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060527183604/http://soapoperadigest.com/Emmys/winners1989/index.html|archivedate=May 27, 2006|title=Daytime Emmy Winners & Nominees: 1989|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]] |publisher=SoapOperaDigest.com|accessdate=August 9, 2009}}</ref><ref name="Emmy 1996">{{cite web|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/Emmys/winners1996/index.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090603195636/http://www.soapoperadigest.com/Emmys/winners1996/index.html|archivedate=June 3, 2009|title=Daytime Emmy Winners & Nominees: 1996|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]] |publisher=SoapOperaDigest.com|accessdate=August 9, 2009}}</ref> McCullough also earned two ''[[Soap Opera Digest]]'' Awards, for Outstanding Youth Actor/Actress in 1986 and Outstanding Child Actor in 1993, as well as a 1987 Young Artist Award.<ref name="SOD stats"/>

In November 2011, McCullough announced her plans to leave ''General Hospital'' in the early months of 2012 to pursue her dream of directing full-time.<ref name=Wrap>{{cite web|title=Kimberly McCullough to Leave 'General Hospital' in Another Blow to Soaps|url=http://www.thewrap.com/tv/article/kimberly-mccullough-leave-general-hospital-32994|work=[[The Wrap]]|publisher=thewrap.com|accessdate=September 9, 2012|date=November 22, 2012}}</ref> This came only weeks after a controversial plot,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefastertimes.com/pop/2011/10/25/hiv-as-a-weapon-has-general-hospital-gone-too-far/|title=HIV as a Weapon: Has 'General Hospital' Gone Too Far?|work=[[The Faster Times]]|publisher=www.thefastertimes.com|accessdate=August 18, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111229193238/http://www.thefastertimes.com/pop/2011/10/25/hiv-as-a-weapon-has-general-hospital-gone-too-far/|archivedate=December 29, 2011|df=}}</ref> where Lisa Niles (portrayed by [[Brianna Brown]]) threatens to inject Robin's blood into her husband, Patrick Drake, which was hard on McCullough and her co-star [[Jason Thompson (actor)|Jason Thompson]] considering Robin's critically acclaimed HIV-story.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2011/10/31/dc-647-jason-thompson-reacts-to-ghs-latest-hiv-storyline-twist-on-the-morning-jolt-with-l |title=Jason Thompson Reacts to GH's Latest HIV Storyline Twist |work=[[Daytime Confidential]] |accessdate=November 21, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111204193806/http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2011/10/31/dc-647-jason-thompson-reacts-to-ghs-latest-hiv-storyline-twist-on-the-morning-jolt-with-l |archivedate=December 4, 2011 |df= }}</ref> While the character was killed off on February 21, 2012, McCullough continued to make several appearances as an apparition in numerous scenes with her loved ones. [[Frank Valentini]], [[Ron Carlivati]] and McCullough discussed her departure, and Carlivati, who was uncomfortable with the idea of Robin being "completely dead", rewrote her story. McCullough's scene on March 27, 2012 showed Robin to be alive, leaving the door open for her to return.<ref name="RobinAlive">{{cite web|url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/news/ghs-ron-carlivati-and-kimberly-mccullough-on-the-decision-to-have-robin-turn-up-alive/2012/03/29/|title=GH’s Ron Carlivati and Kimberly McCullough on the decision to have Robin turn up ALIVE!|date=March 29, 2012|accessdate=April 10, 2012|author=Michael Fairman|work=[[Michael Fairman: On-Air On-Soaps]]}}</ref>

On July 16, 2012, ''[[Soap Opera Digest]]'' announced that McCullough would return to the series for a series of guest spots.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://soapoperadigest.com/content/kimberly-mccullough-back-gh |title=Kimberly McCullough Back To GH! |work=[[Soap Opera Digest]] |publisher=Soapoperadigest.com |accessdate=July 16, 2012 |date=July 16, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://abc.soapsindepth.com/2012/07/robin-returns-to-gh.html |title=Robin Returns To GH! Robin Returns To GH! |last=Simms |first=Richard M. |work=[[ABC Soaps In Depth]] |publisher=ABC.soapsindepth.com |accessdate=July 16, 2012 |date=July 16, 2012}}</ref> She started her series of guest starring spots on July 19, 2012 and lasted until July 27, 2012. In the fall of 2012, Soap Opera Digest confirmed that McCullough would reprise her role as Robin starting on November 6 until December 19, 2012.<ref>{{cite book |chapter=Comings and Goings |title=Soap Opera Digest |page=13 |date=November 13, 2012 |publisher=(Vol. 37, No. 46)}}</ref> She guest-starred for one episode on March 25, 2013, in a video message Robin left for Patrick.<ref>{{Cite episode |series=General Hospital |serieslink=General Hospital |network=[[American Broadcasting Company]] |date=March 25, 2013 |season=49 |language=English}}</ref>

On August 21, 2013, ''Soap Opera Digest'' exclusively confirmed that McCullough had signed a contract to return to the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/digest-exclusive-kimberly-mccullough-returns-gh |title=Digest Exclusive: Kimberly McCullough Returns To GH! |author=SOD |work=Soap Opera Digest |publisher=Soapoperadigest.com |accessdate=August 21, 2013 |date=August 21, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvsourcemagazine.com/2013/08/kimberly-mccullough-returning-to-general-hospital-this-fall/ |title=Kimberly McCullough Returning to ‘General Hospital’ This Fall |last=White-Nobles |first=Omar |work=TV Source Magazine |publisher=TVSourcemagazine.com |accessdate=August 22, 2013 |date=August 21, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/news/breaking-news-kimberly-mccullough-to-return-to-general-hospital-this-fall/2013/08/21/ |title=BREAKING NEWS: Kimberly McCullough To Return To General Hospital This Fall! |last=Fairman |first=Michael |work=Michael Fairman On-Air On-Soaps |accessdate=August 22, 2013 |date=August 21, 2013}}</ref> McCullough made her on-screen return on September 30, 2013. In January 2014, McCullough confirmed her exit from the series once more, last airing on March 4, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last=Clifford|first=Kimbra|title=ON THE RECORD: ‘GH’s’ Kimberly McCullough Says Upcoming Exit Is ‘Not On Good Terms!’|url=http://www.soapoperanetwork.com/2014/01/on-the-record-ghs-kimberly-mccullough-says-upcoming-exit-is-not-on-good-terms|work=Soap Opera Network|accessdate=January 21, 2014|date=January 20, 2014}}</ref> On June 23, 2014, McCullough revealed on her Twitter account that she's received "GH" scripts, this was later confirmed by Valentini that McCullough would be returning as Robin in the summer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abc.soapsindepth.com/2014/06/robins-coming-back-1.html |title=Robin's Coming Back! |last=Simms |first=Richard M. |work=[[ABC Soaps In Depth]] |publisher=ABC.soapsindepth.com |accessdate=August 6, 2014 |date=July 23, 2014}}</ref> Her first airdate back was on August 5, 2014 and she last aired on September 24, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/ghs-robin-returns-today |title=GH'S ROBIN RETURNS TODAY! |author=SOD |work=Soap Opera Digest |publisher=Soapoperadigest.com |accessdate=August 6, 2014 |date=August 5, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite episode |series=General Hospital |serieslink=General Hospital |network=[[American Broadcasting Company]] |date=September 24, 2014 |season=52 |language=English}}</ref> On January 19, 2015, McCullough  guest-starred for one episode as Robin.<ref>{{Cite episode |series=General Hospital |serieslink=General Hospital |network=[[American Broadcasting Company]] |date=January 19, 2015|season=52 |language=English}}</ref> In October 2015, it was announced that she would once again reprise the role of Robin in November. McCullough aired on November 13, 2015, and departed on January 7, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mulcahy Jr.|first1=Kevin|title=Jason Thompson Leaving ''General Hospital'' as Patrick, Kimberly McCullough Returning as Robin|url=http://www.welovesoaps.net/2015/10/jason-thompson-leaving-general-hospital.html|website=We Love Soaps|publisher=[[Blogger (service)|Blogger]] ([[Google]])|accessdate=October 23, 2015|location=United States|date=October 22, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author1=SOD|title=EXCLUSIVE: KIMBERLY MCCULLOUGH ON GH RETURN!|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/exclusive-kimberly-mccullough-gh-return|accessdate=October 27, 2015|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|agency=[[American Media (publisher)|American Media Inc.]]|date=October 27, 2015|location=United States}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |chapter=Comings and Goings: Kimberly McCullough (Robin Scorpio) |title=Soap Opera Digest |pages=11  |date=January 11, 2016 |publisher=(Vol. 41, No. 2)}}</ref>

In April 2016, it was revealed that McCullough was to briefly return for [[Port Charles (fictional city)#The Nurses.27 Ball|The Nurses' Ball]], first appearing on May 9 and departing on May 27.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Giddens|first1=Jamey|title=Lynn Herring and Kimberly McCullough Return For ''General Hospital''{{'}}s Nurses Ball|url=http://daytimeconfidential.com/2016/04/06/lynn-herring-and-kimberly-mccullough-return-for-general-hospitals-nurses-ball|website=[[Daytime Confidential]]|publisher=Confidential Media, Inc. ([[SAY Media]])|accessdate=April 5, 2016|location=United States|date=April 5, 2016}}</ref>

In October 2016, it was revealed that McCullough will be reprising the role, first appearing on October 27 and departing on November 1.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bowe|first1=Jillian|title=Kimberly McCullough Visits ''General Hospital''|url=http://daytimeconfidential.com/2016/10/25/kimberly-mcullough-returns-as-general-hospitals-robin|website=[[Daytime Confidential]]|publisher=Confidential Media, Inc. ([[SAY Media]])|accessdate=November 6, 2016|location=United States|date=October 25, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author1=SOD|title=KIMBERLY MCCULLOUGH CHECKS IN FOR A GH VISIT|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/kimberly-mccullough-checks-gh-visit/|accessdate=November 6, 2015|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|agency=[[American Media (publisher)|American Media Inc.]]|date=October 20, 2016|location=United States}}</ref> In December 2016, McCullough returned for yet another arc, appearing on December 28 and departing on January 19, 2017.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Who's Coming|department=Comings and Goings|pages=12–13|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=[[American Media (publisher)|American Media, Inc.]]|date=January 2, 2017|volume=42|issue=1}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Eades|first1=Chris|title=GENERAL HOSPITAL Confirms the Returns of Ryan Carnes, Kimberly McCullough, and Brooklyn Rae Silzer!|url=http://abc.soapsindepth.com/posts/gh-general-hospital-casting-return-ryan-carnes-kimberly-mccullough-brooklyn-rae-silzer-121705/photos/kimberly-mc-cullough-brooklyn-rae-silzer-220701|accessdate=December 21, 2016|work=[[ABC Soaps In Depth]]|publisher=[[Bauer Media Group]]|date=December 21, 2016|location=United States|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Cushman|first1=Dustin|title=Kimberly McCullough wraps up ''General Hospital'' return|url=http://soaps.sheknows.com/general-hospital/comings-and-goings/1645/kimberly-mccullough-wraps-up-general-hospital-return|website=[[Soaps.com]]|publisher=[[SheKnows Media]]|accessdate=February 6, 2017|location=United States|date=January 27, 2017}}</ref> McCullough reappeared from February 20, 2017 until March 10, 2017.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Who's Coming|department=Comings and Goings|page=12|date=February 27, 2017|volume=42|issue=9|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=[[American Media (publisher)|American Media, Inc.]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author1=SOD|title=ROBIN RETURNS TO GH|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/robin-returns-gh/|accessdate=February 20, 2017|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=[[American Media (publisher)|American Media, Inc.]]|date=February 20, 2017|location=United States}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Cushman|first1=Dustin|title=Kimberly McCullough finishes another brief return to ''General Hospital''|url=http://soaps.sheknows.com/general-hospital/comings-and-goings/1667/kimberly-mccullough-returns-to-general-hospital-2|website=[[Soaps.com]]|publisher=[[SheKnows Media]]|accessdate=March 20, 2017|location=United States|date=March 17, 2017}}</ref>

In April 2017, Valentini revealed that McCullough was back on-set of the soap for further appearances.<ref>{{cite news|author1=SOD|title=Robin And Emma Pop In To GH|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/robin-emma-pop-gh/|accessdate=April 21, 2017|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|agency=Odyssey Magazine Publishing Group Inc.|publisher=[[American Media Inc.]]|date=21 April 2017|location=United States}}</ref> McCullough returned for two episodes on May 18 and 19.<ref name=GH051817>{{Cite episode |series= General Hospital |series-link= General Hospital |credits= [[Jean Passanante]] and [[Shelly Altman]] ([[Head writer]]s); [[Scott McKinsey]] ([[Television director|Director]]); Katherine Schock ([[Screenwriter|Script writer]]) |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date= May 18, 2017 |season=55 |language= English}}</ref><ref name=GH051917>{{Cite episode |series= General Hospital |series-link= General Hospital |credits= [[Jean Passanante]] and [[Shelly Altman]] ([[Head writer]]s); [[William Ludel]] ([[Television director|Director]]); Scott Sickles ([[Screenwriter|Script writer]]) |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date= May 19, 2017 |season= 55 |language= English}}</ref>

In November 2017, it was announced that McCullough would reprise the role again to facilitate [[Steve Burton (actor)|Steve Burton]]'s return to the series.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.soapsindepth.com/posts/gh-general-hospital-kimberly-mccullough-casting-return-116768/photos/gh-robin-patrick-01-127731|title=Kimberly McCullough Returns to GENERAL HOSPITAL!|first=Chris|last=Eades|work=[[Soaps In Depth#ABC Soaps In Depth|ABC Soaps In Depth]]|publisher=[[Bauer Media Group]]|date=November 10, 2017|accessdate=November 16, 2017}}</ref> McCullough returned on November 17 and departed on December 4.<ref name=GH111717>{{Cite episode |series= General Hospital |series-link= General Hospital |credits= [[Shelly Altman]] and [[Chris Van Etten]] ([[Head writer]]s); Denise Van Cleve ([[Television director|Director]]); Charlotte Gibson ([[Screenwriter|Script writer]]) |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date= November 17, 2017 |season= 55 |language= English}}</ref><ref name=GH120417>{{Cite episode |title= |series= General Hospital |series-link= General Hospital |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=December 4, 2017 |season= 55 |credits = [[Frank Valentini]] ([[Executive producer]]); [[Shelly Altman]] and [[Chris Van Etten]] ([[Head writer]]s)}}</ref>

McCullough returned from February 6 to 13, 2018, for the funeral of [[Nathan West (General Hospital)|Nathan West]].<ref name=GH020618>{{Cite episode |series= General Hospital |series-link= General Hospital |credits=[[Frank Valentini]] ([[Executive producer]]); [[Shelly Altman]] and [[Chris Van Etten]] ([[Head writer]]s) |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date= February 6, 2018 |season= 55 |number= 13967 |language= English}}</ref><ref name=GH020918>{{Cite episode |series= General Hospital |series-link= General Hospital |credits=[[Frank Valentini]] ([[Executive producer]]); [[Shelly Altman]] and [[Chris Van Etten]] ([[Head writer]]s) |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]|date= February 9, 2018 |season= 55 |number= 13970 |language= English}}</ref><ref name=GH021318>{{Cite episode |series= General Hospital |series-link= General Hospital |credits=[[Frank Valentini]] ([[Executive producer]]); [[Shelly Altman]] and [[Chris Van Etten]] ([[Head writer]]s) |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]|date= February 13, 2018 |season= 55 |number= 13972 |language= English}}</ref> In April 2018, it was reported that McCullough would made a short-term appearance for the Nurses Ball.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Eades|first1=Chris|title=Kimberly McCullough Returns to General Hospital!|url=https://www.abc.soapsindepth.com/posts/gh-general-hospital-kimberly-mccullough-casting-return-116768/photos/gh-robin-patrick-01-127731/|accessdate=May 25, 2018|work=[[ABC Soaps In Depth]]|publisher=[[Bauer Media Group]]|date=April 24, 2018|location=United States}}</ref> McCullough made her return from May 16 to 21, 2018.<ref name=GH051618>{{Cite episode |series= General Hospital |series-link= General Hospital |credits=[[Shelly Altman]] and [[Chris Van Etten]] ([[Head writer]]s); [[Phideaux Xavier]] ([[Television director|Director]]); [[Kate Hall (soap opera writer)|Kate Hall]] ([[Screenwriter|Script writer]]) |network= [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date= May 16, 2018 |